<br>
I'm very good at anything having to do with English and writing and no good at all with math. People who are good with math usually aren't good with English, but can see all these numbers in their head and making everything into an equation helps them understand things better. I think the majority of the people who looked at your chart are like me and didn't get it. <br>
<br>
At first it looked like you were saying those percentages related to an increase in that particular skill, when in actuality they just represented the increase per point. Yes going from skill level 2 in Natural Healing to skill level 3 increases your regen by 1 hp per tick, but each point you spent is only worth 0.16 hp's, whereas each point from the previous level gain was worth 0.25 hp's. So for 2 more levels of work you reap less of a reward.<br>
<br>
Maybe putting it into words instead of calculations will help the folks that think like me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urekcim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rekcim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/22/01 9:24:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13547.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Table of skill point to skill effect efficiency</span><hr size=1> The % he lists is simply how much increase you get PER SKILL POINT.  If he lists .83%, that means you get .83% increase per skill point you had to put into it.  <br>
<br>
.83*6 skill points=5% total gain over previous level.<br>
<br>
Maybe do the chart and put +.83% per skill point.<br>
